reviews.review_text: I visited North Vancouver District the first time just to try the food here. Honestly, they are best fish and chips Ive ever had better others Ive had in Greater Vancouver! The in-house tartar sauce was sooo delicious as well (can squeeze out as much as I want); it had a fresh, tarty dill taste. The onion rings and oyster were good. And the tomato juice was tasty and refreshing. The mushy peas, however, were not my cup of tea (it, to me, is like a coarse base puree thats just salted). It was quite the satiating lunch; perfect for going to a hike trail afterward.  Moreover, I did not need to eat dinner. As for the service, its excellent. I liked the waitress personality; shes chill and accommodating.

A great quick service, clean, one of the best in Greater Vancouver Area for those fish lovers, eat as much as you can meal also comes with unlimited refill for Pepsi products, coleslaw is great, onion rings and sauces. Enjoy the fresh fish & chips!

$20 all you can eat fish and chips! The only way to go! The pieces of fish are similar in size to chicken fingers, so not huge. Not sure it would be worth it to get the one piece meal for $16 or $17, but with the all you can eat, its a no brainer. Also comes with bottomed bottomless soda if thats your thing.

I like to come here sometimes after hiking very hungry and tired. The All-you-can-it fish and chips + a sleeve of a delicious Okanagan Spring beer, is a really good deal. The delicious food, the great service, the cleaning and the nice environment make this place a fresh spot to stay. Thank you!
Always love to come here. The all you can eat is great mad they always make it fresh. It is very basic yet very tasty. Recommended dishes All-You-Can-Eat Fish and Chips

Nice light and crispy fish and chips. We used to go here for all you can eat which was a good deal. The food is fresh and the service is good. Recently with COVID we ordered the Takeout Special which includes 2 pounds of fish, a big load of chips, a 2 litre pop, and coleslaw. Was packaged nicely, ready when we arrived to pickup. Enough for two meals for our family of four with younger kids. Great deal.

Id say C-Lovers is one of the better fish and chips places in Vancouver. I would recommend getting the haddock over the cod as they are very similar in flavour, especially after being deep fried, but the haddock is a larger portion.
A very pleasant suprise! The batter on the fish was so light and flaky. Its one of the best fish and chip places Ive ever been to.
I love the deep fried dill pickles! and also the platter was so good
Very good fish and chips and simple but great coleslaw. They have Haddock which is what my wife likes. They serve beer and wine also. The service was great and prices pretty good too.
Great fish and chips!  Large tasty piece of fish perfectly battered and fried.  Fries are great! Customer service was awesome and I would highly recommend this place for a first date!
Love this place..I always get all you can eat...I have been going to this place for years now..best seafood on the northshore

The go to place for AYCE Fish & Chips with bottomless pop. Service is friendly... you dont have to have fish & chips refill, you can just choose fish for your refill. Great value & the fish is good. They used pollock, meat is firm. Batter is light & not greasy.

Everything excellent. The minute you walk in the door they take your name and ph# for contact tracing tables approprately spaced out plexiglass seperation sanitizer a must before being seated. Servers are friendly and aaaaaefficient!!!!. The all you can eat fish and chips, tarter sauce and coleslaw is the best i have had. Kennebec fries fresh hot and crispy fish without too much batter. They have a great team from the servers  cooks & dishwasher. I highly recommend this C-lovers. I give them a 5+++++
Not elaborate but well run. Good F&C at (still) reasonable prices. Excellent, friendly & helpful service.
One of the best fish and chips in Vancouver

Never really had real fish and chips until I found this gem. Everything here was freaking delicious.   The onion rings here are amazing! But not as amazing as the different types of fried fish here. Will definitely visit again when Im around the area! Didnt know there were multiple locations of this place around Vancouver.
I liked the cuisine, the service, and the ambiance. I like professionalism and customer care standards, which should remain to the top. Another visit is required here!
Excellent food, cute little place but the service should be more friendly in the dining area. Parking: Good
One of the best i ve ever tried!!
We placed a largish take out order, and they made everything ontime and hot and fresh.  Everyone was very happy! Parking: Lots of free parking.

The halibut burger is the best fish burger Ive ever had! The house made tartar sauce is unbeatable. I made a pickup order and they waited until I got there to give me a piece of fish fresh out of the fryer  . One of my favourite spots in the city.
Authentic fish and chips! Friendly staff, delicious seafood! Loved our experience there and came out with super happy bellies!
Cheerful, hard-working folks, Fish is prepared, perfectly fresh change of cooking oil, pleasant waitresses

Amazing place with an all you can eat fish and chips option. It is very good quality for the quantity as well, and the servers were always smiling. Nothing much more can be asked of a place. Do make sure to go here with a big appetite, I am sure you will enjoy the fish!
Not too expensive, good fish and good chips. Great place for inexpensive fish etc. Onion rings were great Parking: Lot of parking in lot near
Consistently great takeout.  Big portions, reasonable prices, quick service.  Great tartar sauce.  The premium fish options are worth it and the oysters are the best.

THIS IS LITTERALY THE BEST RESTERANT IN THE UNIVERSE. ALL OTHER RESTURANTS CAN EAT -- as a local guide, it would be irisponsible for me to finish this sentance :) -- I LOVE YOU SO MUCH THOUGH EVERY YEAR I COME HERE AND I GET MY BIG MAGICAL MEAL. I CAN LITTERALY NOT EXPRESS MY GRATITUDE FOR THIS PLACES EXISTANCE. MY GRANDMA WENT HERE, MY MUM WENT HERE, MY DAD WENT HERE, C-LOVERS MAKES THE FINEST FISH AND CHIPS IN THE GALAXY. GRAAAAAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHHH SDZAKSDZAWK,SDKHJ,DSZKHJZSDJKDJHKMZDXSCJHMKXDCJMHKZXCDSJMHKCJKMHMH

The fish and chips were really good, but I think the customer service is outstanding! Props to our server Jayden for being so attentive and considerate. We had ordered all you can eat and bottomless drinks. Whenever our drink is almost finished, she appears out of nowhere with a new one ready! The atmosphere had all smiles too! It is the little things
SO tasty! I ve reviewed before and will continue reviewing it every time I have their fish and chips because it s the best one in Vancouver.
Reliable choice for great fish and chips. All you can eat is good value but at the expense of eating their premium fish which is worth spending a little more for. Great place for kids however.
The fish batter is just in the right amount, not greasy, but a bit sweet. Great fish and chips overall.

As a Brit we can confirm this is the closest thing you can get to british fish and chips in the lower Mainland. Love this place, get a bread roll with you meal so you can make a fish butty. Also the chicken is fab too.
Good food, good fast service. Best fish n chips in town - not greasy, just crispy & delicious. Yummy fresh coleslaw too. I always feel young when I come here since its usually full of seniors.

Went to C-lovers for their all you can eat fish and chips special and it was really good! The fish they use is polluck and the peices of fish are quite meaty and the batter wasnt too overpowering. I like that they start you off with 5 pieces of fish and a half plate of fries versus other places that basically give a full plate and two pieces. The servers were also super nice and very friendly which made the experience even better!
Great seafood and the staff are very friendly and take good care of you.

Gotta be a 5-star. Have been a few times lately and the food has always been great. Very good portions of perfectly cooked fish and chips with the batter done to perfection. Ive also had the C-dog and the chicken strips and those are great.

Can be quite a wait when they are busy, but thats a sign of a good restaurant with good quality food. When you order an All You Can Eat meal, make sure you put in your refill a bit earlier as it can take a while before you get it. Parking: Unfortunately a couple of businesses closed down in this area, but as a result, more parking spots are available!
Fast great fish. Best fish and chips in town
Great food and super service! Love it!
Waitress wasnt the greatest and its was super crowded but still one of my fams fav restaurants for all you can eat fish and chips!!
Enjoyed the one piece Haddock which was more than enough. Challenge yourself with the 17.99$ all you can eat. Super quick service and fully licensed. Great fish.
Very nice place for fish and chips at reasonable prices. I always get the all you can eat special and generally have quick and friendly service from their server Shou.

We ordered the cod and salmon 2-piece dinners and they were fantastic. I was both surprised and excited after noticing the fish was very lightly breaded with large pieces of fish. The ratio of fish to breading was perfect.  The coleslaw and fries were also delicious. Perfect fuel for after a Grouse Grind hike! :)

Awesome place! The all you can eat fish and chips with bottomless drink included is the best deal in town. The fish and chips are incredible and they have the tastiest tartar sauce they bring to the table by the bottle full. A True all you can eat experience and one of the best menus for what youre craving.
Food was pretty good, service was great. Overall excellent experience!

Best Fish and Chips in Town! They have all you can eat and have great value all round. Parking: Free parking lot right out front. Kid-friendliness: This is a family friendly restaurant. Wheelchair accessibility: it is on the main floor so it is wheelchair accessible.
A nice fish and chip shoppe with an all you can eat and pop option Kid-friendliness: Discounted kid s meals by age Food : 4/5 |
Delicious fish and chips ( halibut) nice atmosphere. friendly guys.

Always worth the trip. Even though the price went up by about 30%, the all-you-can-eat fish & chip meal (including bottomless pop) is still a very good deal. Everything was very fresh & tasty, and our server was very friendly & attentive.

I enjoy All You Can Eat menu of C-Lovers. Unlimited hot and well breaded fish with fries and bottomless pops. There is lots of free parking in front of this place. I appreciate Rose for warm welcome and service.
Went for the all you can eat and the portions were huge! Nice and crispy not too greasy, chips were good. Staff was super friendly and attentive! Would def eat here again when the cravings hit.

All you can eat cod fish n chips was the bomb. I had 6 pieces to myself and I was so satisfied. The halibut fingers were amazing too. The freshness of the fish really came through and the fries were heavenly. The onion rings were beautiful too and everything went well with that amazing tartar sauce. Coffee is free flow. Id recommend this place in a heartbeat.

Excellent Fish and Chips. I always go for the Halibut, and ask for extra lemon. The place closes early by restaurant standards but maybe it is because it caters to an older crowd.  The drink menu is quite limited so I dont choose to dine in. We always do takeout...and the food is always consistently good. The service is prompt and the staff pleasant. Its the best F&C on the North Shore!!
Our go-to fish n chips on the north shore. Lovely fish, fries and Caesar salad.

Fantastic! A great place for fish and chips. They have a great takeout menu and a nice dine-in layout. We ordered takeout and were very satisfied with the portions, cost, and service. Will be ordering from them in the future.
Food was fantastic.  Our waitress and other staff were super friendly.  Prices were reasonable.  Will definitely come back!

Great place for fish n chips! Lovely lady at front of the house, awesome gentleman at the back and very friendly server. Strongly recommend at least to try cod. We all enjoyed every single chip and delicious cod.

All you can eat fish and chips. Tack on a bottomless pop, and its heaven. Too bad that Im older now, so the food gets a little bit greasy and heavy. However its me and not them. When you have the AYCE, you need to add salt and pepper to taste. They provide ketchup and tartar sauce.
Best fish and chips you can find Northshore. Very fresh fish and great service.  can be very busy at lunch time.
A great meal of all you can eat fish and chips with coleslaw salad. Also bottomless pop is included in the AYCE fish & chips. I really enjoyed the tasty meal.

Delicious! The taste and the portions are really good, they offer different types of combos or plates for sharing. The onion rings are amazing. The food is fresh, the service is fast, friendly staff, nice and quiet place. They have kids many. Recommendations for the place, you can have more types of dressings. (Mayo, something spicy).
All you can est is a lot, just choose 3-4 strips of fish and thats all.

Probably the best fish and chips Ive ever had. It was recommended to us by friends and ...wow! We had haddock and halibut.   I preferred the haddock and its less expensive  as well.  Id go there next time Im visiting in the area again.
Great staff, always friendly. Never a hassle getting take out. They are flawless with their fish, Ive never had a bad order from them. Ive probably ordered 12 times over the last year.

Great fish and chips.  This spot is thin on atmosphere but if you want a traditional fish and chips menu this is the place to come.  Fills early with a more senior crowd and very family friendly.  Take out is busy all the time.  Best in town.

Great place, great fish and great service!! Thanks for the good times C Lovers North Van! The waitress is very nice. Still trying to beat my first all you can eat record number of fish pieces, maybe next time :)
The halibut family size fish and chips were delicious and well worth the cost. The staff were very friendly too

Great fish and chips. The servers are friendly. They are considered ocean wise which is good. There menu is rather limited, but what do you expect from a restaurant named fish and chips? We went during a slow time and the food was still amazing.
Had the 2 PC halibut dinner. It came moist and perfectly battered and cooked .delicious! Chips were the same and great service. Reasonable price for the quality  . Ill be back!
Friendly welcoming and serving throughout the meal and most importantly the food was delicious! It was packed around 6-7pm on a weekend night. Will have more visits in the future!
Good family restaurant. Food was really good. The server was a bit flustered, as I think she was new. She did well though.

Generous portions, fresh and tasty. Casual, clean and excellent service. Family of 3 we ordered a haddock burger, cod meal and a large caesar salad for lunch. We wish we lived closer so we could visit more often.
Love their fish and chips deal for take out. Feeds a family of four and you can request their homemade tartar sauce. So delicious!
Yes it was very filling the 2 pic cod was awesome

Fish and chips is the soul food of the West Coast, there are times your soul just desires it. I order piece of fish and fries with a small gravy to go, along with nice amount of malt vinegar. They paper wrap the food, no plastic! ! No seasoning is needed, batter is near perfect in constancy, cannot wait to try the AYCE option they have when Covid is over.

Happy New Year     To All my Friends & Relations. I grew up near Steveston BC.  Ive tried alot of different deep fried fish    C- Lovers  is on the Top of my list. Delicious, Consistent ,They Always get it right ! I enjoy 1 PC. cod ( for me huge portion ) & 6 PC. Jumbo shrimp   dinner with fries ,gravy ,always ask for condiments & extra accessories., They always give Very Generous ,Fast!  Worth the Drive .
Great food, generous portions of fish. The all-you-can-eat fish-n-chips is great value if you have a big appetite. Clean and cosy restaurant. Wheel chair accessible. However parking is very limited.
Loved the Cod fish and chips here!!!!!!! Best place in Vancouver but in north van lol

Absolute best fish and chips and if youre not into fish then they have the best chicken fingers youll ever have. Theyve spoiled me. Now no other chicken measures up to theirs. Hey, they even make a hot dog (corn dog) with the same scrumptious batter they put on their fish or chicken. Its a bit hidden behind the bushes behind the Shell service station at Pemberton and Marine. Reasonably priced, its become our go to weekly dinner out.

I have been going to this restaurant for over a decade and the quality has been consistently great. Their all you can eat is still a good deal, but these days I settle for a 1 piece cod meal which is enough to satisfy my fish and chips craving.

The first I had fish and chips in C-Lovers was back in 2004 since then I go there very often. Love the food, their great customer service and the peaceful environment. I highly recommend C-lovers to all seafood lovers

Good to see the north shore location persevered through the last couple years.  Staff are always hustling and working hard!  Great fish & chips!  Busy busy...always a good sign of a good spot to dine!
Im impressed and surprised. Never knew about this place until a few days ago. The staff did a great job. The food was excellent! Thanks and see you soon!
First time customers. Will definitely return. We got the take away special. It was a ridiculous amount of food, all of which was delicious.  Friendly, quick service. Happy new customers!

I go here with my family occasionally;  They have never, EVER dissapointed us.  The fish tastes super fresh, their foods are barely greasy, the crisp is amazing, and if youre going there, I recommend the All you can eat meal.  Endless tasty fish! What more could you want!  Call me greedy, but everytime I go there, we all see who can eat the most.  Usually, no more than 5 pieces, since they fill you up, but boy are they delicious. Plus, they have such great staff!  I recommend going here when you can! Best possible way to spend 15$. p.s Get the onion rings too!  Theyre great!

C-Lovers is by far the best fish and chips in North Vancouver. I highly recommend the Halibut although it is a bit pricy. Still it is absolutely delicious and since going to C-Lovers its become impossible for me to enjoy random fish and chips at a pub or some other restaurant. I also love that they wrap their Togo orders in paper + newspaper, a real throwback to the old days. No matter what kind of fish you get C-Lovers is the place to go in North Van. Just be warned, it may ruin everything else for you like it did for me!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow! Thanks so much for the awesome review! We hope to see you again!

reviews.review_text: The BEST fries, cole slaw, home made tartar sauce, fries (did I say fries twice? Yes! Theyre that good!) and of course.....the beautifully battered fish, especially love the halibut but their cod and haddock are fantastic too. Chicken strips! Dont forget to try their moist, delicious chicken strips. Very large portions too! And a good tip for left over fries.....take them home! Yes! Pop them in the freezer wrapped in newspaper then a few days later, bake them like theyre McCain frozen fries. Nom!!
Favorite place on the North Shore for some great fish n chips. Never disappoints for me or my dining guest(s).  Have always returned and left satisfied - Cheers!

Excellent food, no waiting to be seated.  Very friendly staff. The plaxe is spacious and clean. If there was a restaurant like this on Marpole it would be my favorite. Too bad this pkace is too far from home.

2011 July update. Just as excellent as ever. The best haddock and chips Ive had in a long time. Thick, juicy and full of flavour. Next time Ill ask for only a half order of chips. Great lightly battered fish accompanied with hand cut chips...plus very friendly staff...$13.99 AYCE Cod and Chips & Pop

The best fish and chips Ive ever had. Consider ordering the ALL YOU CAN EAT fish and chips...you will not regret it. Will definitely come back to this restaurant on mu next visit to North Vancouver...

Very affordable ayce fish and chips. Im quite sad their downtown location closed down as this north Van establishment is very far from my home. Try not to over eat! Five stars because I feel like I get more than what I paid for. Also the service is very nice!

Great food! Fast service and a wonderful cashier. Better than fish and chips at a fancy restaurant. If you want something tastey and fast this is the spot!!!!! Even wrapped in newspaper its the best!!!!

Whenever I take my Grandma out for lunch I take her to C-Lovers. For some reason old people just love this place. Everything here is reasonable priced. Just remember to arrive early before lunch, because thats when all the seniors come for their fish and chips.
Had a lovely meal here on a Friday night. Mushy peas and coleslaw were excellent!
If you love halibut n chips, or cod n chips, then this place should be your goto place like it is mine. A little pricy but the quality out ways the price! The atmosphere is always spot one.
Great value for money. Really good fish n chips considering its an all you can eat joint. I was definitely surprised. Highly recommended

Their Take-Out Special is worth it! Youll get surprised how much youd get with what you pay. I like very good deals. : ) You can search on their website and order ahead by calling on the contact# by location.
Fast service, good quantity, great taste
